  <title>Student Services</title>

  <subsection xml:id="accommodations_for_students_with_disabilities">
    <title>Accommodations for Students with Disabilities</title>
    <p>
      Students needing testing or classroom accommodations based on a disability must be registered with the Louisiana Tech University Office of Testing &amp; Disability Services. Students are encouraged to discuss those needs with the instructor as soon as possible. If you do not have a current accommodation memo, visit the <url href="https://www.latech.edu/current-students/student-advancement-affairs/disability-services/">Office of Testing &amp; Disability Services for assistance.</url>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="counseling_services">
    <title>Counseling Services</title>
    <p>
      Students have access confidential counseling services at no additional cost.
      Visit the <url href="https://www.latech.edu/current-students/student-advancement affairs/counseling-services/">Louisiana Tech Counseling Services</url> website to learn more. 
    </p>
  </subsection>

